@host = https://localhost:7219
@token = 

### Health Check
GET {{host}}/health

### 1. Create User
POST {{host}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "john.doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "+5511999999999",
  "password": "StrongPass123!",
  "role": "Admin"
}

### 2. Authenticate User
POST {{host}}/api/auth
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "StrongPass123!"
}

### 3. Create Sale (Protected - Requires Authentication)
POST {{host}}/api/sales
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "saleNumber": "SALE-001",
  "saleDate": "2024-01-15T10:00:00Z",
  "customerId": "customer-123",
  "customerName": "John Customer",
  "branchId": "branch-456",
  "branchName": "Main Branch",
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": "product-789",
      "productName": "Premium Product",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 99.99
    }
  ]
}

### 4. Get All Sales (Protected - Requires Authentication)
GET {{host}}/api/sales?page=1&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get Specific Sale (Protected - Requires Authentication)
GET {{host}}/api/sales/{{saleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Update Sale (Protected - Requires Authentication)
PUT {{host}}/api/sales/{{saleId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "customerId": "customer-123",
  "customerName": "John Customer Updated",
  "branchId": "branch-456",
  "branchName": "Main Branch",
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": "product-789",
      "productName": "Premium Product",
      "quantity": 3,
      "unitPrice": 89.99
    }
  ]
}

### 7. Cancel Sale Item (Protected - Requires Authentication)
POST {{host}}/api/sales/{{saleId}}/items/{{itemId}}/cancel
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "reason": "Customer requested cancellation"
}

### 8. Delete Sale (Protected - Requires Authentication)
DELETE {{host}}/api/sales/{{saleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Get User by ID (Public)
GET {{host}}/api/users/{{userId}}

### Notes:
# 1. Replace {{token}} with the actual JWT token from the auth response
# 2. Replace {{saleId}} with an actual sale ID
# 3. Replace {{itemId}} with an actual item ID
# 4. Replace {{userId}} with an actual user ID
# 5. All Sales endpoints require authentication (Bearer token)
# 6. User endpoints are public (no authentication required)
